pestering a ManU player for an autograph at a chip shop lol
summary: Foster tells a nice and typically self-deprecating story of his time at Manchester United. For weeks he would be pestered for...
text: Foster tells a nice and typically self-deprecating story of his time at Manchester United. For weeks he would be pestered for autographs by a young, snappily-dressed kid at a chip shop near his house in the Cheshire village of Holmes Chapel. Years later, Foster and his wife saw him on TV. The kid had grown to become someone rather famous, Harry Styles of One Direction. ‘I have never heard from him since,’ says Foster, laughing. 'Like most United fans, he probably can’t remember me!’
source: Former England goalkeeper Ben Foster talks about meeting young Harry (x)
